WEBVTT

1
00:01:32.820 --> 00:01:35.060
All together now!

2
00:01:36.020 --> 00:01:41.220
There's a centipede on a peg...

3
00:01:41.620 --> 00:01:43.540
and here's a...

4
00:01:44.340 --> 00:01:45.580
leg!

5
00:01:45.780 --> 00:01:48.540
Bravo, great!

6
00:01:49.380 --> 00:01:54.020
There's an owl flying over the bed...

7
00:01:55.180 --> 00:01:57.900
Everybody do the owl!

8
00:01:58.060 --> 00:02:00.500
And here's the head!

9
00:02:00.620 --> 00:02:03.700
Excellent, you're doing great.

10
00:02:03.980 --> 00:02:08.100
There's a bee with a stinger...

11
00:02:08.740 --> 00:02:10.620
and here's a...

12
00:02:10.980 --> 00:02:12.260
finger!

13
00:02:12.780 --> 00:02:14.340
Grześ, your finger!

14
00:02:14.420 --> 00:02:15.420
Your finger.

15
00:02:15.580 --> 00:02:17.500
Finger. Finger!

16
00:02:31.380 --> 00:02:33.140
It's a piece of junk.

17
00:02:33.260 --> 00:02:37.940
It was found near Kętrzyn,
in the Wolf's Lair.


18
00:02:38.300 --> 00:02:40.780
Hitler's headquarters.

19
00:02:43.940 --> 00:02:46.020
This tinklebox is a piece of history!

20
00:02:46.220 --> 00:02:50.660
I've lived with him for years and still
don't know what he feels or thinks!


21
00:02:50.900 --> 00:02:55.300
He wants to make contact with me,
tell me things, but doesn't know how.


22
00:02:55.740 --> 00:02:56.740
He doesn't know anything!

23
00:02:57.180 --> 00:03:00.020
But what he's come to understand
is that he wants to know everything.


24
00:03:00.260 --> 00:03:02.180
He's sure damn curious of the world!

25
00:03:02.340 --> 00:03:06.900
He's seen his brother do maths, biology
you know, school subjects!


26
00:03:07.100 --> 00:03:10.220
And so it begins!
How am I supposed to explain to him,


27
00:03:10.620 --> 00:03:11.940
if he doesn't understand a thing!

28
00:03:12.460 --> 00:03:14.700
- He just doesn't get it!
- Make some space.


29
00:03:15.820 --> 00:03:17.660
Go ahead and press it.

30
00:03:17.940 --> 00:03:19.180
Go on.

31
00:03:20.340 --> 00:03:21.780
No, press here.

32
00:03:24.100 --> 00:03:26.460
He observed it somewhere.
He figured it out himself!


33
00:03:26.540 --> 00:03:27.860
He did it all by himself.

34
00:03:27.940 --> 00:03:30.980
It's a real lift, isn't it?
He sure has some engineering skills.


35
00:03:31.140 --> 00:03:33.700
So I say: bloody hell,

36
00:03:33.980 --> 00:03:35.780
they're making a mistake somewhere!

37
00:03:35.980 --> 00:03:37.340
Who are you talking about?

38
00:03:37.460 --> 00:03:40.620
The people at the disabled centre.
He learns there.


39
00:03:40.740 --> 00:03:42.116
Come on, that's not proper learning!

40
00:03:42.140 --> 00:03:44.180
Each duck makes a funny face

41
00:03:44.220 --> 00:03:47.540
Dancing all around the place
Quack, quack, quack!


42
00:03:47.940 --> 00:03:51.340
When the ducks do the swing
They shake their wings


43
00:03:51.500 --> 00:03:53.180
And their rump...

44
00:03:53.260 --> 00:03:54.900
Quack, quack, quack!

45
00:04:03.620 --> 00:04:06.860
They keep telling us that there's
no bright future for Grześ!


46
00:04:07.260 --> 00:04:10.340
That nothing can be done!
But I'm the one who lives with him.


47
00:04:10.500 --> 00:04:15.380
Here's why we're looking for
a support teacher.


48
00:04:17.300 --> 00:04:19.180
It has to be
a professional from outside.


49
00:04:19.300 --> 00:04:22.060
One who's not entangled
in this whole system of relationships.


50
00:04:22.220 --> 00:04:24.540
Also, one who can stand him.

51
00:04:25.460 --> 00:04:27.500
And how many haven't?

52
00:04:43.380 --> 00:04:44.380
Hoo-hoo!

53
00:04:45.220 --> 00:04:46.300
Come here!

54
00:04:46.460 --> 00:04:47.460
Hoo-hoo!

55
00:04:49.340 --> 00:04:50.660
Come!

56
00:04:54.740 --> 00:04:56.060
Hello, Grzesiek.

57
00:04:56.540 --> 00:04:57.540
I'm Krystyna.

58
00:04:57.580 --> 00:04:59.300
This is Michał.

59
00:04:59.500 --> 00:05:01.140
And this is Grześ.

60
00:05:03.540 --> 00:05:07.220
Let's go yum-yum!
Michał, please take him away!


61
00:05:07.380 --> 00:05:09.980
Yum-yum!
Come on, Michał, help me...


62
00:05:11.980 --> 00:05:12.980
See, this man is playing.

63
00:05:13.500 --> 00:05:14.500
You see?

64
00:05:14.580 --> 00:05:18.420
Let's listen, do you hear me?
Come on, let's go, let's listen.


65
00:05:18.540 --> 00:05:19.660
Let's go.

66
00:05:23.940 --> 00:05:26.180
Grzesiek, come on,
it's an old piece of junk!


67
00:05:26.420 --> 00:05:29.780
It only takes up space!
Małgośka, help me!


68
00:05:32.660 --> 00:05:34.500
Małgośka, help me!

69
00:05:53.060 --> 00:05:54.060
Fuck!

70
00:05:55.900 --> 00:05:56.900
Grzesiek?!

71
00:05:57.380 --> 00:05:59.540
What do you think you're doing?!

72
00:06:30.740 --> 00:06:31.740
Grześ,

73
00:06:32.340 --> 00:06:33.340
take a look.

74
00:06:39.300 --> 00:06:41.900
Do you know why I'm here?

75
00:06:42.180 --> 00:06:44.300
It's because we will study together.

76
00:06:44.940 --> 00:06:46.460
First we'll learn about each other.

77
00:06:46.940 --> 00:06:49.060
You learn about me, 
I learn about you.

78
00:06:49.740 --> 00:06:52.860
Then we will learn
to count, to write...


79
00:06:53.860 --> 00:06:56.580
I'll tell you
why the sun shines,


80
00:06:57.340 --> 00:06:59.260
why the moon shines,

81
00:06:59.980 --> 00:07:02.100
why one shines during the day,

82
00:07:02.980 --> 00:07:05.460
why the other one shines at night...

83
00:07:06.980 --> 00:07:08.100
I'll tell you...

84
00:07:13.060 --> 00:07:14.060
Take it easy.

85
00:07:16.380 --> 00:07:17.380
Take it easy.

86
00:07:19.500 --> 00:07:20.580
We've got time.

87
00:07:41.540 --> 00:07:42.540
Grzesiek!

88
00:07:43.380 --> 00:07:44.380
Grzesiek!

89
00:07:45.540 --> 00:07:48.340
Grzesiek, come on.
Let's go back to our lesson.


90
00:07:48.780 --> 00:07:51.100
Let's not get upset now,
because then I won't find out


91
00:07:51.260 --> 00:07:56.020
what you're going on about,
and you won't learn anything.


92
00:07:56.100 --> 00:07:57.100
Wait!

93
00:08:10.340 --> 00:08:11.340
Grzesiu.

94
00:08:12.220 --> 00:08:14.500
Look at me!
Look at me.


95
00:08:16.860 --> 00:08:18.660
Are you listening to me?

96
00:09:15.460 --> 00:09:18.700
New strings,
they're still unstable.


97
00:09:19.580 --> 00:09:24.860
It will need to be retuned
two or three times.


98
00:09:25.540 --> 00:09:29.020
When you play it afterwards...

99
00:09:29.220 --> 00:09:30.340
I won't.

100
00:09:30.860 --> 00:09:32.060
My son will.

101
00:10:53.700 --> 00:10:57.340
He'll get over it.
He'll get over it soon.


102
00:11:56.900 --> 00:11:58.820
Have you painted your whole hand?

103
00:11:59.020 --> 00:12:00.380
All of it, properly?

104
00:12:00.740 --> 00:12:01.740
Show me.

105
00:12:03.620 --> 00:12:06.020
Now let's make a handprint,

106
00:12:06.300 --> 00:12:07.540
let's press firmly.

107
00:12:12.380 --> 00:12:14.460
This is your little finger.

108
00:12:15.900 --> 00:12:16.900
Grześ?

109
00:12:17.100 --> 00:12:19.300
Look at me and repeat.

110
00:12:19.780 --> 00:12:21.020
Look at my lips.

111
00:12:21.540 --> 00:12:22.540
Little!

112
00:12:24.500 --> 00:12:25.500
Little.

113
00:12:27.500 --> 00:12:28.740
Please repeat.

114
00:12:28.940 --> 00:12:30.260
Little.

115
00:12:31.620 --> 00:12:33.340
What's the finger like?

116
00:12:34.020 --> 00:12:35.620
Grześ, what's the finger like?

117
00:12:36.020 --> 00:12:37.020
Little.

118
00:12:39.500 --> 00:12:41.420
Let's try again.
Look.


119
00:12:41.860 --> 00:12:43.180
Large, medium...

120
00:12:44.620 --> 00:12:45.620
little!

121
00:12:56.620 --> 00:12:59.100
- Michał, you're disturbing us.
- You can always leave, Miss.


122
00:12:59.220 --> 00:13:01.380
I can't, I'm working.

123
00:13:01.580 --> 00:13:03.460
Grześ, look at me.

124
00:13:04.220 --> 00:13:05.220
Grzesiek!

125
00:13:06.380 --> 00:13:07.380
Hoo-hoo, neh-neh!

126
00:13:09.540 --> 00:13:10.780
What happened?

127
00:13:10.980 --> 00:13:11.980
Nothing!

128
00:13:16.220 --> 00:13:19.860
Please focus
and let's try again.


129
00:13:20.580 --> 00:13:23.060
Little.
Little finger.


130
00:13:28.380 --> 00:13:29.700
Grzesiek!

131
00:13:29.980 --> 00:13:31.100
Would you like to play?

132
00:13:31.260 --> 00:13:32.340
Would you like to play?

133
00:13:32.820 --> 00:13:34.540
Would you like to play the piano?

134
00:13:34.740 --> 00:13:36.660
Would you like
to play the piano?


135
00:13:36.900 --> 00:13:39.980
You would, right?
So pick up the sheet of paper.


136
00:13:41.180 --> 00:13:43.180
Go ahead, pick it up from the floor.

137
00:13:43.340 --> 00:13:45.060
Put it on the desk, here.

138
00:13:46.460 --> 00:13:50.340
Pick up the sheet
from the floor and put it on the desk.


139
00:13:54.180 --> 00:13:57.100
Instructions
assisted by gestures...


140
00:13:57.340 --> 00:14:00.060
We'll go and play in a while,
wait a second.


141
00:14:02.900 --> 00:14:05.260
Are something he understands,
he even complies with them.


142
00:14:05.420 --> 00:14:09.380
But speaking to him with no gestures
just doesn't...


143
00:14:10.020 --> 00:14:13.500
His hearing simply isn't
as it should be.


144
00:14:14.380 --> 00:14:16.940
Do you really think
we didn't suspect it?


145
00:14:17.420 --> 00:14:19.340
We've been visiting doctors for years.

146
00:14:19.460 --> 00:14:21.060
Michał, have you washed your hands?

147
00:14:21.340 --> 00:14:23.940
Łukasz,
they hit Michał with a ball.


148
00:14:24.020 --> 00:14:25.460
- Again?
- So?


149
00:14:26.300 --> 00:14:29.660
- They're taunting him as a lowlander.
- Or as one who's all thumbs!


150
00:14:30.180 --> 00:14:33.620
But I'm asking you
what the doctors said.


151
00:14:34.100 --> 00:14:35.180
The same thing.

152
00:14:36.300 --> 00:14:40.580
He can hear, but he's autistic,
and autistic children don't react.


153
00:14:40.940 --> 00:14:44.140
With all due respect,
I work with autistic children.


154
00:14:45.660 --> 00:14:49.460
Perhaps this opinion about Grzesiek
is worth revising.


155
00:14:55.940 --> 00:14:59.420
Medical certificate: autism,
April 1993.


156
00:15:03.100 --> 00:15:05.780
When did you go
to Krakow with him? In 1996, 1997?


157
00:15:05.900 --> 00:15:06.900
I don't remember.

158
00:15:09.220 --> 00:15:11.900
This is from a neurologist,
another certificate:


159
00:15:12.180 --> 00:15:13.180
Autism.

160
00:15:16.220 --> 00:15:17.860
Now let's see: hearing.

161
00:15:19.620 --> 00:15:22.500
Specialised Hearing Clinic,
here you go.


162
00:15:22.740 --> 00:15:24.860
September 1996.

163
00:15:25.740 --> 00:15:29.860
But what if you assumed
that Grześ is not autistic?


164
00:15:30.180 --> 00:15:33.740
October 1998,
he had his hearing acoustics tested


165
00:15:33.860 --> 00:15:34.860
in Nowy Targ.

166
00:15:35.420 --> 00:15:39.260
All private visits,
it all cost money, 100 zlotys each.


167
00:15:39.700 --> 00:15:40.860
What do we see written here?

168
00:15:41.180 --> 00:15:42.260
Hearing: normal!

169
00:15:42.420 --> 00:15:45.620
But could you please assume
that Grześ is not autistic?


170
00:15:45.820 --> 00:15:50.580
Look here, in Rabka,
they referred us for an EEG.


171
00:15:50.980 --> 00:15:52.620
At the Provincial Hospital,
in November...


172
00:15:59.620 --> 00:16:01.380
Grześ, pick up the knife please.

173
00:16:02.700 --> 00:16:03.700
Grześ!

174
00:16:04.340 --> 00:16:05.340
Pick up the knife!

175
00:16:31.980 --> 00:16:34.420
I'd have him examined again.

176
00:16:34.660 --> 00:16:35.820
While he's asleep.

177
00:16:38.460 --> 00:16:40.660
- While he's asleep?
- Yes, exactly.


178
00:16:41.300 --> 00:16:43.220
Without involving his consciousness.

179
00:16:48.300 --> 00:16:51.500
Try to close your eyes,
to calm down.


180
00:17:01.060 --> 00:17:02.460
Close your eyes please.

181
00:17:34.980 --> 00:17:38.140
Are you saying
that everyone was wrong?


182
00:17:38.700 --> 00:17:39.620
No, I'm not.

183
00:17:39.700 --> 00:17:43.380
What I'm saying is that your son
does perceive sound.


184
00:17:44.020 --> 00:17:46.020
In the low registers.

185
00:17:47.460 --> 00:17:50.500
He's autistic, that's true,
but he's not deaf!


186
00:17:50.820 --> 00:17:54.100
He plays the piano
using not only the low ones...


187
00:17:54.460 --> 00:17:58.380
In the high registers,
he feels vibrations,


188
00:17:58.980 --> 00:18:02.620
which is sufficient for him
to play music, but...


189
00:18:03.340 --> 00:18:04.820
it's not enough

190
00:18:05.420 --> 00:18:06.500
to develop speech.

191
00:18:08.300 --> 00:18:09.300
Please,

192
00:18:09.740 --> 00:18:10.980
plug your ears now.

193
00:18:11.620 --> 00:18:12.620
Come on,

194
00:18:12.900 --> 00:18:13.980
do it.

195
00:18:16.100 --> 00:18:17.100
Here you go.

196
00:18:21.740 --> 00:18:23.940
And thus, for all these years,

197
00:18:24.820 --> 00:18:27.260
he's been unable to hear the radio,

198
00:18:27.820 --> 00:18:30.460
the telephone ringing,
or you, for that matter.


199
00:18:31.020 --> 00:18:35.460
The concept of a “word”
has never crossed his mind.


200
00:18:35.980 --> 00:18:40.340
Language, in fact, develops
by the age of five or six.


201
00:18:41.940 --> 00:18:42.940
Today...

202
00:18:43.340 --> 00:18:45.780
your son has his own world,

203
00:18:46.780 --> 00:18:49.860
he somehow navigates it in his own way.

204
00:18:51.780 --> 00:18:54.260
He lives an inner life.

205
00:19:18.420 --> 00:19:19.420
Grzesiek?

206
00:19:27.700 --> 00:19:29.060
Grzesiek...

207
00:19:30.140 --> 00:19:32.060
Can you hear me?

208
00:19:44.500 --> 00:19:47.180
That's right,
you're the one hearing this, Grześ.


209
00:19:47.460 --> 00:19:48.780
It's your voice!

210
00:19:55.500 --> 00:19:57.140
It's all right, Grzesiek.

211
00:19:57.220 --> 00:19:58.220
Grzesiek!

212
00:19:59.180 --> 00:20:00.820
It's all right.

213
00:20:35.460 --> 00:20:36.460
Come, Grzesiek.

214
00:23:03.380 --> 00:23:04.380
Michał!

215
00:23:06.340 --> 00:23:07.380
Call Grzesiek!

216
00:23:08.660 --> 00:23:10.260
- Hoo-hoo!
- No, wait.


217
00:23:14.740 --> 00:23:16.820
No more “hoo-hoos”.

218
00:23:17.780 --> 00:23:21.220
Go to him and say:
Grzegorz, dinner is served.


219
00:23:21.780 --> 00:23:22.980
- Repeat after me.
- Łukasz!


220
00:23:23.260 --> 00:23:26.060
- He won't understand him.
- Repeat after me.


221
00:23:26.340 --> 00:23:27.780
Dinner is served.

222
00:23:28.060 --> 00:23:29.060
No.

223
00:23:29.780 --> 00:23:30.780
Grzegorz,

224
00:23:31.620 --> 00:23:32.740
dinner is served.

225
00:23:33.020 --> 00:23:34.300
- I'll go.
- Don't!


226
00:23:34.540 --> 00:23:36.940
He has to learn his own name.

227
00:23:37.460 --> 00:23:39.540
Grzegorz, dinner is served.

228
00:23:43.140 --> 00:23:44.220
Dinner is served.

229
00:23:57.140 --> 00:24:00.100
From now on, you'll address him
normally.


230
00:24:00.500 --> 00:24:01.900
Like any other person.

231
00:24:02.540 --> 00:24:04.700
And this person has a name.

232
00:24:05.220 --> 00:24:06.220
What is it?

233
00:24:07.500 --> 00:24:08.500
It's Grzegorz.

234
00:24:21.700 --> 00:24:22.700
Hoo-hoo!

235
00:24:24.180 --> 00:24:25.380
Hoo-hoo!

236
00:24:30.540 --> 00:24:32.860
Grzegorz, dinner is served.

237
00:24:34.500 --> 00:24:37.300
Grzegorz, dinner is served.

238
00:24:39.580 --> 00:24:40.820
Grześ! Aaaa!

239
00:24:41.020 --> 00:24:42.020
Dinner!

240
00:24:42.140 --> 00:24:43.420
Is served!

241
00:24:48.500 --> 00:24:49.500
Hoo-hoo!

242
00:24:57.460 --> 00:24:58.860
Here's where you switch it off,

243
00:24:58.980 --> 00:25:00.140
you press here

244
00:25:00.300 --> 00:25:01.500
to fast-forward!

245
00:25:02.060 --> 00:25:03.580
Here's rewind...

246
00:25:04.700 --> 00:25:05.900
You stop it here.

247
00:25:14.140 --> 00:25:15.460
You take it out like this.

248
00:25:15.580 --> 00:25:16.980
You take it out!

249
00:25:58.300 --> 00:26:00.140
My son is not handicapped,

250
00:26:00.220 --> 00:26:02.340
although that's what we were told.

251
00:26:02.620 --> 00:26:04.740
They deceived us!

252
00:26:05.460 --> 00:26:06.460
They deceived us.

253
00:26:06.980 --> 00:26:09.260
I'm not sure
if you were necessarily deceived.


254
00:26:09.420 --> 00:26:10.500
I don't know that.

255
00:26:11.940 --> 00:26:13.220
Krystyna,

256
00:26:13.500 --> 00:26:14.900
you're really trying hard,

257
00:26:14.940 --> 00:26:16.820
your intentions are good.

258
00:26:17.700 --> 00:26:22.300
But don't defend them,
because I'll think you're in cahoots.


259
00:26:22.460 --> 00:26:26.540
There's a lot of money that follows
this autistic Grześ of ours.


260
00:26:26.820 --> 00:26:28.220
This money's not for Grzesiek.

261
00:26:28.300 --> 00:26:29.660
It's not for us.

262
00:26:29.780 --> 00:26:30.780
It's for them.

263
00:26:31.860 --> 00:26:35.060
It didn't pay for them
to diagnose him correctly.


264
00:26:35.220 --> 00:26:36.900
Inconceivable, isn't it?

265
00:26:38.620 --> 00:26:39.660
