01:38:21.700 --> 01:38:23.420
Even unintentionally.

1078
01:38:29.860 --> 01:38:30.860
Grześ!

1079
01:38:32.340 --> 01:38:34.780
Justynka is here to see you.

1080
01:38:38.300 --> 01:38:39.860
No, no, no.

1081
01:38:40.700 --> 01:38:44.540
You couldn't pick up the phone,
but you could have called back.


1082
01:38:44.780 --> 01:38:48.260
Maybe I had something
very important to tell you.


1083
01:38:48.860 --> 01:38:53.620
I started playing again for you,
after not playing for a long time.


1084
01:38:53.940 --> 01:38:57.340
And don't apologise,
justice will be done to you anyway.


1085
01:38:57.420 --> 01:39:00.500
You'll get the punishment
that you deserve!


1086
01:39:00.980 --> 01:39:03.340
You're not God,
you can't punish me.


1087
01:39:03.540 --> 01:39:04.740
Don't apologise.

1088
01:39:04.820 --> 01:39:08.420
I don't need you anymore
and you can leave.


1089
01:39:08.740 --> 01:39:11.100
You can get out of this house!

1090
01:39:11.460 --> 01:39:13.660
Admit it, you're a fraud.

1091
01:39:14.020 --> 01:39:17.220
You're a fraud,
and I had a present for you.


1092
01:39:17.460 --> 01:39:19.620
Because I am good to you.

1093
01:39:19.900 --> 01:39:23.820
For you I have learnt to play
the most beautiful piece


1094
01:39:23.980 --> 01:39:25.900
ever created in this world:

1095
01:39:26.180 --> 01:39:28.180
"The Moonlight Sonata"!

1096
01:39:28.620 --> 01:39:31.980
It's played as if the moon
reflected itself in a lake


1097
01:39:32.020 --> 01:39:35.580
and now I see
that the lake is full of tears!


1098
01:39:36.140 --> 01:39:40.780
Go on, you can leave now
and never come back!


1099
01:39:40.860 --> 01:39:43.780
You didn't deserve it anyway!

1100
01:41:36.220 --> 01:41:38.460
Show me where to cut it,
you choose!


1101
01:41:38.580 --> 01:41:40.820
We can't give you more time.

1102
01:41:40.980 --> 01:41:44.500
That wouldn't be fair
towards the others.


1103
01:41:45.060 --> 01:41:47.340
We had a deal: three minutes, right?

1104
01:41:47.660 --> 01:41:50.460
- Did we have a deal? We did.
- You don't get it...


1105
01:41:50.740 --> 01:41:51.740
You don't get it.

1106
01:41:51.900 --> 01:41:56.020
You can't perform unless you meet
all the criteria.


1107
01:41:56.860 --> 01:41:57.900
It's as simple as that.

1108
01:41:57.940 --> 01:42:00.180
You're not performing!

1109
01:42:00.580 --> 01:42:02.340
So, what will it be?

1110
01:42:04.060 --> 01:42:05.100
Three minutes?

1111
01:42:06.420 --> 01:42:07.420
Three.

1112
01:42:10.820 --> 01:42:12.180
Put it on.

1113
01:42:14.300 --> 01:42:15.300
OK?

1114
01:42:16.300 --> 01:42:17.380
Come here!

1115
01:42:39.300 --> 01:42:42.100
This was Natalia Jasińska.

1116
01:42:42.380 --> 01:42:44.300
She sang an old song

1117
01:42:44.700 --> 01:42:47.060
from the Kurpie region.

1118
01:42:47.660 --> 01:42:50.420
And here's another competitor

1119
01:42:51.220 --> 01:42:53.100
from Poland.

1120
01:42:53.620 --> 01:42:56.100
He can hear thanks to an implant

1121
01:42:56.620 --> 01:43:00.780
with a flexible

1122
01:43:01.660 --> 01:43:04.140
Today, he will perform for you

1123
01:43:04.540 --> 01:43:09.100
a part of the first movement
of "the Moonlight Sonata"


1124
01:43:09.260 --> 01:43:11.180
by Ludwig van Beethoven.

1125
01:43:11.580 --> 01:43:14.460
Ladies and Gentlemen,
Grzegorz Płonka.


1126
01:45:45.780 --> 01:45:49.540
Grzegorz Płonka won
the festival Beats of Cochlea.


1127
01:45:54.460 --> 01:45:58.020
After that the world heard of him.

1128
01:46:03.940 --> 01:46:10.180
Two years later, at the age of 29,
Grzegorz graduated from music school.